---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { t } from '../../i18n/utils';

const locale = 'en';
---

<PageLayout locale={locale} title="Privacy Policy | Tiny House Heavens" description="Privacy policy of Tiny House Heavens. Read how we protect your personal data in compliance with GDPR.">

  <section class="pt-32 pb-16 bg-gradient-to-b from-thh-green-50/50 to-thh-cream">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 text-thh-charcoal">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-thh-charcoal/50">Last updated: March 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-thh-cream">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 prose prose-lg prose-thh">

      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12 shadow-sm space-y-8 text-thh-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed">

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-thh-charcoal mb-4">1. Data Controller</h2>
          <p>Tiny House Heavens<br/>Fort 15<br/>2860 Sint-Katelijne-Waver, Belgium<br/>VAT: BE0403.670.250<br/>Email: info@tinyhouseheavens.com<br/>Phone: +32 465 600 263</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-thh-charcoal mb-4">2. What data do we collect?</h2>
          <p>We collect the following personal data when you contact us or request a quote:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 mt-3">
            <li>Name</li>
            <li>Email address</li>
            <li>Phone number (optional)</li>
            <li>Messages and correspondence</li>
            <li>Model preference and project information</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-thh-charcoal mb-4">3. Purpose of processing</h2>
          <p>Your personal data is processed for the following purposes:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 mt-3">
            <li>Answering your questions and requests</li>
            <li>Preparing and sending quotes</li>
            <li>Execution of agreements</li>
            <li>Improvement of our services</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-thh-charcoal mb-4">4. Legal basis</h2>
          <p>The processing of your personal data is based on:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 mt-3">
            <li>Your consent (contact form)</li>
            <li>Execution of an agreement</li>
            <li>Legitimate interest (improvement of services)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-thh-charcoal mb-4">5. Retention period</h2>
          <p>We do not retain your personal data longer than necessary for the purposes for which they were collected. Contact details are kept for a maximum of 2 years after last contact, unless an ongoing agreement or legal obligation requires a longer retention period.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-thh-charcoal mb-4">6. Your rights (GDPR)</h2>
          <p>In accordance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), you have the right to:</p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1 mt-3">
            <li>Access your personal data</li>
            <li>Rectification of incorrect data</li>
            <li>Erasure of your data</li>
            <li>Restriction of processing</li>
            <li>Data portability</li>
            <li>Object to processing</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">You can exercise these rights by contacting us at info@tinyhouseheavens.com.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-thh-charcoal mb-4">7. Cookies</h2>
          <p>Our website uses functional cookies that are necessary for the proper functioning of the website. We do not use tracking cookies or third-party cookies for advertising purposes.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-thh-charcoal mb-4">8. Complaints</h2>
          <p>If you have a complaint about the processing of your personal data, you can contact the Data Protection Authority (GBA):<br/>Drukpersstraat 35, 1000 Brussels<br/>contact@apd-gba.be<br/>www.gegevensbeschermingsautoriteit.be</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</PageLayout>
